The paper focuses on the analysis of deep neural networks (DNNs) in the kernel regime, which is a common topic in the machine learning community and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the effect of initialization and loss functions on the generalization error of DNNs, which is a topic related to optimization and neural networks, and falls under the categories of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions regression problems and experiments with image data, which are related to computer vision and fall under the category of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper proposes an initialization trick that improves the training of DNNs, which is related to control and optimization and falls under the category of "cs.SY" (Systems and Control).
